# Cloudflare Pages redirects — processed BEFORE static assets & Functions.
#
# WHY: a stale static index.html (left over from the old Next.js deployment)
# kept being served at "/" because Cloudflare prioritises static assets over
# the Pages Function. _redirects rules run FIRST, so a rewrite here always wins.
#
# Rule 1 — rewrite "/" to the "/home" Function route. The URL in the browser
#          stays "palmkit.app/" (200 = silent proxy, not a redirect). The
#          Function (functions/[[path]].ts → app/routes/home.tsx) renders the
#          Landing for logged-out visitors and the Chat for logged-in ones.
/ /home 200

# Rule 2 — anyone who bookmarked "/home" during the previous band-aid is
#          forwarded to the clean "/" URL. (Does NOT loop: rewrites do not
#          re-evaluate _redirects rules, so the internal proxy from rule 1
#          never hits this rule.)
/home / 302
